Day 0: PlayWright Setup
	npm - Node packaging manager
	Q: Different ways we can install sowftware
	Ans: 1. npn install <<library name>>
		2. npn i <<library name>>
		3. npn init <<library name (Recomended)>>
		
	Installing Playwrigt
	1. npm init playwright (installs latest version)
	2. npm init playwright@1.56.1 (Install Specific version)
	3. npm init playwright@latest (install latest version)
	3. npm init playwright@latest (install latest version)
		
	Commands will use in PlayWright
	1. npx playwright test - to run end to end test
	2. npx playwright test --ui - Start the interactive UI mode
	3. npx playwright test --project=chromium - Runs the test only on Desktop chromium
	4. npx playwright test --example - runs the test in specific file
	5. npx playwright test --debug - Run test in debug mode
	6. npx playwright test codegen - auto generate test with codegen
	
	PlayWright file details
	1. github\workflows - this files contains the pipeline details linked to Github. all the tasks mentioned what to do when new DEV codebase is pushed to github
	2. node_modules - it is the heart of the module. when we install playwright, this file will be created. if this file is deleted. Playwright will not work.
		"./node_modules\playwright\test.mjs" this file contains list of all the files which we can import based on the need.
	3. tests - this is the default location to write test scripts
	4. tests-examples - contains sample tests 
	5. .gitignore - Here we can mentions all the files which should not to pushed to GitHub.
	6. package-lock.json - This files provides all the details of the playwright installation and dependencies done so far
	7. package.json - This file is used to control the execution flow. something like regression suite.
		"scripts": {} - This if where we will mention the execution flow
	8. playwright.config.ts - Most important file. Most of the settings we will do in this file like headless mode, parallel execution etc.
		 This will be explained in next session/video.
	
	
	For any authorization for playWright, use below command
		set-ExecutionPolicy -Scope CurrentUser
		-ExecutionPolicy RemoteSigned
		
	Important files to refer in Playwright framework
	1. PlayWrght_Proj_JSTS\node_modules\playwright\test.mjs
	2. PlayWrght_Proj_JSTS\tests\example.spec.ts
	
Day 1:	Understanding Playwright configuration and Parallel testing
	List of parameters we work with in this file
	1. import { defineConfig, devices } from '@playwright/test'
		In order to work with below parameters, we need to import respective packages/modules.
		defineConfig & devices are mentioned in "./node_modules\playwright\test.mjs" file
		
	2. testDir
		Path of the test script files. when we execute "npx playwright test" command, then playwright will execute 
		all the test cases written under this path.

	4. forbidOnly
		if you are running scripts via CICD pipeline then in that case if anywhere if "this.only" is mentiond in any
		of the test case then that particular test case will execute but the execution will fail. because regression
		suite means executing multiple test cases, not only one test case.
	5. retries
		you can mention how many times you want to re-execute the failed test cases
	
	7. reporter - type of report you want to generate (html/list/dot/line/github/json/junit/null)
	
	8. Use - Play applies all the properties/settings inside this USE to each test case.
		NOTE - what ever settings or rules you want to set at each test case level, need to be mentioned under "USE" 
		keyword. "USE" keyword is also available under "Project"
		
		trace - off/on/on-first-retry/on-all-retries/retain-on-failure/retain-on-first-failure
		screenshot - off/on/only-on-failure/on-first-failure
		video - off/on/retain-on-failure/on-first-retry
		headless - true/false (by default is is TRUE)
		
	9. projects - Browser details which Playwright supports (it supports 7 types of brwosers)
	
	3. fullyParallel
	6. workers - describes how many test case should run in parallel
		
Day 2: Understanding Playwright Architecture, Test annotation and async-await concept
		Playwright uses WebSockets to communicate with Browser
		
